entries.femaleVariant: Can't believe they bothered to truck it all the way out here.
Eh, better than the junkyard where I landed.
entries.maleVariant: It's better than the junkyard where I landed.

entries.femaleVariant: "Cast a cold eye, on life, on death,"
"Horseman, pass by!"
Let's go, NC beckons.
What'd you expect? Headstone, flag and flowers?
Nah, I... I dunno. A marker?
Something, anything.
[Inscribe Johnny's initials] Let's do something about that.
Really need a symbol?
Better now?
Really need symbolic, empty gestures?
So that's how it is.
[Sit] D'ya expect a headstone?
Nothing here at all.
Guess I do. Thought I'd feel like I'd closed a chapter here.
Like I'd said goodbye to the old Silverhand, hello to the new.
A bit. But let's say it was my real grave – what would you write?
"Here lies Johnny Silverhand--"
"Relentless Rockerboy."
"Night City Legend."
"Terrorist and Raging Asshole."
"The Guy who Saved My Life."
And how do you feel?
Like I never even was. Or like I was still inside Mikoshi.
"Relentless Rockerboy Who Never Surrendered." Not even in death.
"Night City Legend."
"Terrorist and Raging Asshole."
"The Guy who Saved My Life."
Thanks. But what's that do for me now?
Sounds good. But what does it really mean?
Harsh.
But if I saw a headstone like that, I'd wanna meet the guy.
V... You don't know how much I want that to be true.
What's gotten into you?
What'd I achieve fighting Arasaka?
Won't win this war alone.
So many dead – and those suits're still on top.
What did I achieve, shouting "Chippin' In" to a bunch of angry, pimply kids?
Gave 'em hope.
Now you're just whinin'.
Just feeling sorry for yourself.
What's gotten into you all of a sudden?
What's gotten into you?
Listen, I realize I fucked up a lotta things.
That wasn't a compliment.
Did you just come here to feel sorry for yourself?
Won't win this war goin' solo.
Might be a good thing we're in this together.
That's just it. Don't wanna drag you down into this swamp with me.
Just feeling sorry for yourself.
Ya gave those kids hope. That the suits couldn't buy everything.
I remember what I thought on stage. That even if they all died for their ideals, it'd be worth it.
No. Just finally thinking clearly.
Where's Johnny I'm-the-fuckin'-greatest Silverhand? Don't even recognize you.
entries.maleVariant: Where's Johnny I'm-the-fucking-greatest Silverhand? Don't even recognize you.

entries.femaleVariant: Maybe I'm done pretending.
But when I look at you...
A hard road, but looks like we made it.
Nah, fucked that up too.
Johnny, no need to bare your soul to me.
Been a long, bumpy road, but we made it.
entries.maleVariant: It's been a long, bumpy road, but we made it.

entries.femaleVariant: No, Johnny. You fucked that up, too.
You used me, lied to me... Can't trust you at all.
entries.maleVariant: You used me, lied to me... I can't trust you at all.

entries.femaleVariant: Ahem, is it too late to ask for a second chance?
No need to confess all your wrongs to me, Johnny.
I know. But maybe I want to.
Too late. This was your second chance.
What do you want from me?
Too late. This was your second chance.
You died, came back and still had no idea what to do with it all.
Think you're right.
What d'you want from me?
Most people I thought were my friends, they couldn't even stand to be in the same room with me.
You're fuckin' closest to me by a long shot. There twenty-four seven.
And yet... you don't seem to hate my living guts.
At least, so it seemed… till now.
You were a real dick in the beginning.
OK. But as second chances go, this is your last.
It's not hate… Just had enough of you.
OK. But as second chances go, this is your last. I refuse to be that naive.
I'll try damned hard.
Don't hate you… just had enough. Look at you – still trying to manipulate me.
entries.maleVariant: I don't hate you, I just... had enough. Look at you – still trying to manipulate me.

entries.femaleVariant: Shit. I really fucked up.
Can we go now?
Sure, won't keep you. Wanna go see Hanako, set things up?
Yeah. Eventually.
Heh. Johnny Silverhand. Terrorist and Raging Asshole.
V. First among suckers.
Shame we didn't talk like this earlier.
You were a real dickwipe at first.
Hah. Johnny Silverhand. Night City Legend.
Johnny Silverhand. Relentless Rockerboy Who Never Gives Up.
Too bad we didn't talk like this earlier. Woulda made things easier.
entries.maleVariant: It's too bad we didn't talk like this earlier. Woulda made things easier.

entries.femaleVariant: Never found the right moment.
Didn't mean that as a compliment.
entries.maleVariant: Didn't mean it as a compliment.

entries.femaleVariant: I know.
Remember wakin' up at Viktor's, not knowin' about me? "I'm seeing things, I'm scared."
Still feel like you can't breathe?
Remember you whinin' for smokes in the middle of the night, complainin' about not bein' able to kill me.
entries.maleVariant: Remember you whinin' for smokes in the middle of the night? Complainin' about not bein' able to kill me.

entries.femaleVariant: Then moanin' at Misty's 'bout how you didn't wanna die?
You sorta deserved it.
Never thought we'd make it this far.
When you said you let down your friends...
When you said you let your friends down – did ya mean Rogue?
Still feel like you can't breathe in here?
Nah. Not sayin' it's great, but it's different.
Sometimes when I wake up, feels like I'm back for a while.
Well, like I got this body to myself. Like I'm free.
Seconds later, feels like I'm missing something – something really important.
What d'you mean – back?
Then I realize you're there, always were, and this stupid wave of relief washes over me.
When you said you let your friends down...
Have the same dreams...
Have similar dreams sometimes. That you never died, that I'm you.
entries.maleVariant: I have similar dreams sometimes. That you never died, that I'm you.

entries.femaleVariant: Not like I think, "What would Johnny do?" It's more I do something and I feel... fuckin' great.
Like I've finally started to fit into this world.
Hm, prolly not a great sign. We better do something. Fast.
Rogue, Alt, Kerry, Santiago...
Not all's lost yet, least with Rogue.
Can't pretend nothing's changed over fifty years, can't just insert myself into her life.
C'mon, already have.
Smasher biz really got to her.
Smasher biz really got to her. Can't leave it like this, I don't think.
entries.maleVariant: Smasher biz really got to her. Ya can't leave it like this, I don't think.

entries.femaleVariant: C'mon, already have.
True, that.
Might be right. She was acting weird.
Y'know, did promise her I'd take her to the movies. Long, long ago.
You oughta talk to her.
Good idea.
Call her for me, ask if she's free some night?
Thing is, you'd have to surrender control – again.
Yeah, I'll call Rogue.
Forgot about that…
Yeah, I'll call her.
Forgot about that.
Just an idea. Won't press it.
OK.
Let's delta. Nothin' to see here after all.
OK.
Worth comin' out all the same?
Absolutely. Thanks, V.
Of all the heads I coulda popped up in, hella glad it was yours.
Funny. Place is familiar. Made a pit stop here once.
entries.maleVariant: Funny. Place is familiar. I made a pit stop here once.

entries.femaleVariant: Why here?
Used to be a nomad fridge set up here for people on the road. Take a beer, leave a beer from your region in return.
entries.maleVariant: There used to be a nomad fridge set up here for people on the road. Ya take a beer, leave a beer from your region in return.

entries.femaleVariant: Mhm.
Look. Still here.
A fridge.
We'll figure something out.
Either let down or used every last person who gave me their trust. Blind, selfish bastard that I was.
But I've managed one thing for now. Not to fuck this up, what we have.
Know you're not fond of me, yeah.
To put it mildly.
Ooh, another serious talk.
An' that's mildly put.
But, ooh, another big talk. Not a fan of those, either.
Can tell you're tryna be disarmingly honest. Keep goin', tell me what this is really about.
Want you to give me a second chance.
Let down my friends, showed you the worst of me.
I noticed. Been watchin' you for some time now.
OK. Just one last request.
Request? Think this is a good time?
I'm listening.
Request? Seriously? This seem like a good time to you?
entries.maleVariant: Request? Seriously? Does this seem like a good time to you?

entries.femaleVariant: OK. Just go to North Oak – whenever you think it's a "good time."
I'm listening.
Take me to North Oak.
What for?
Kerry. Tell you more once you get me there.
OK.
Been here.
[Stand]
[Stand]
